{"key":"post-12427979","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12427979</id>\n<content>&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Stillmatic9142 said:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Should the frosting layer be mixed in with the top of substrate or just sprinkled lightly on top?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Neither.&amp;nbsp; The idea of 'frosting' is bad practice.&amp;nbsp; Don't have any exposed grains on the surface.&amp;nbsp; Doing so leads to a higher incidence of contamination because the grains dry out, which weakens the mushroom mycelium, allowing molds like trichoderma to enter the exposed grains.&amp;nbsp; Make sure you always have a layer of substrate or casing material over any grains.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12427997</next>\n<prev>12427915</prev>\n<first>12427635</first>\n<last>12428237</last>\n<when>1271809011</when>\n<utime>04/21/10 03:16 AM</utime>\n</post>"}